# Knowledge Map

A **Vue 3** project that visualizes a knowledge map using **Vis.js**.

## ğŸš€ Installation & Setup (Linux)

Follow these steps to install and run the project on a **Linux system**.

### **1ï¸âƒ£ Install Node.js & npm**
Ensure you have **Node.js** and **npm** installed. If not, install them:

#### **Ubuntu/Debian**
```bash
sudo apt update && sudo apt install nodejs npm -y
```

#### **Fedora**
```bash
sudo dnf install nodejs npm -y
```

#### **Arch Linux**
```bash
sudo pacman -S nodejs npm
```

---

### **2ï¸âƒ£ Clone the Repository**
```bash
git clone https://github.com/YOUR_GITHUB_USERNAME/knowledge-map.git
cd knowledge-map
```

---

### **3ï¸âƒ£ Install Dependencies**
```bash
npm install
```

---

### **4ï¸âƒ£ Run the Development Server**
Start the Vue development server:
```bash
npm run dev
```

This will output a local development URL, such as:
```
  Local:   http://localhost:5173/
```

Open your browser and visit **http://localhost:5173** to see the application running.

---

## ğŸŒŸ Running as a Background Process
If you want to keep the server running after closing the terminal:
```bash
nohup npm run dev > output.log 2>&1 &
disown
```
This will run the process in the background and store logs in `output.log`.

